@node main "DrivePrefs 1.1"

 DrivePrefs 1.1 by David Watson
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  - an all-in-one anti-click, drive delay and retry settings command!
  - can even stop your drives clicking during startup!
  - 100% assembly language!
  - only 844 bytes!
  - a pure command - can be made resident!
  - absolutely free!


 @{"         Description         " link Description}
 @{"  Distribution & Disclaimer  " link Distribution}
 @{" Requirements & Installation " link Install}
 @{"            Usage            " link Usage}
 @{"        DIRE WARNINGS        " link Usage 111}
 @{"     Calculating Timings     " link Timings}
 @{"           History           " link History}
 @{"           Author            " link Author}
@endnode

@node Description

 Description
 ~~~~~~~~~~~
  DrivePrefs is a small CLI command to change the settings of trackdisk
device floppy drives (i.e. normal floppy drives), allowing you to set the
head step, settle and calibrate delays, number of retries on a damaged
track, and to stop the drive click.

 Driveprefs can be run at the very beginning of your startup, and can stop
your drives clicking @{b}IMMEDIATELY@{ub}, unlike WBStartup Commodities or even any
of the other CLI no-click utilities I've seen. With a fast drive, you need
never hear another click during your startup, ever again!
@endnode

@node Distribution "Distribution and Disclaimer"

